## Clause 0 Introduction
1. 概述
2. 與其他管理系統標準之相容性

### 概述
* 本標準乃是為了提供建立、實施、維護與持續改進一個資訊安全管理系統 (Information Security ManagementSystem, ISMS) 的要求而籌備的。
* 組織的 ISMS 之設計與實施受其需求與目標、安全要求、所採用的過程以及組織之規模及架構所影響。這些要素的全部預期會隨時間而改變。**並不是希望所有導入ISO 27001的機構制度都一樣**
* ISMS 透過一個風險管理架構的適用，來保護資訊的機密性、完整性與可用性，且此資訊安全被列入充分管理的考量裡。
* 本標準適用於包含驗證機構的內部與外部團體，藉以評鑑組織達成自身資訊安全要求的能力。
* ISMS 是組織過程和總體管理架構的一部份並結合了兩者，且此資訊安全被列入過程的設計、資訊系統與管控的考量裡。期望 ISMS 的實施與組織的需求相稱，例如：簡單的情況只需簡單的 ISMS 解決方案。
* 在本標準裡呈現的要求之先後並非代表其重要性以及實施的順序。所列的項目僅供參考。
* ISO/IEC 27000 描述了 ISMS 的概述與詞彙，形成 ISMS 標準系列的主軸 (包含ISO/IEC27003、ISO/IEC 27004和ISO/IEC 27005)，且定義出相關的用語釋義。
### 與其他管理系統標準之相容性
* 本標準適用了ISO/IEC Directives，Part 1 綜合 ISO 補充中的附錄 SL 所明定的高層次架構、相同的子條款標題、相同的文本、共通用語與核心定義，因而維持與其他已採用附錄 SL 的管理系統標準之相容性。
* 附錄 SL 所明定的共通作法，對於那些選擇運作可滿足兩種或多種管理系統標準的要求之單一管理系統，將是非常有用的。


## Clause 1-2-3 of ISO 27001:2013 standard
The first three clauses of ISO 27001:2013 Standard describe the scope of this standard normative, references and the terms and definitions used in this standard.
> ISO 27001：2013標準的前三個條款描述了本標準的範圍，參考標準以及本標準中使用的術語和定義。

![](https://i.imgur.com/XiJEfP6.png)


### Clause 1 - Scope

#### This international standard specifies requirements for an ISMS when an organization:
>本國際標準規定了一個組織對ISMS的要求:
1. Uses it to proactively improve information security (ISMS) performance and prevent incident related to information security;
> 1.用它來主動提高資訊安全（ISMS）的性能和防止與資訊安全有關的事件；
2. Seeks to manage ISMS responsibilities in a systematic manner to contribute to the sustainability of ISMS pillar.
> 2.尋求系統地管理ISMS職責以促進ISMS支柱的可持續性。
3. This international standard is intended to be applicable to any organization regardless of size, type and nature.
> 本國際標準旨在適用於任何組織，無論大小，類型和性質
#### 適用範圍補充
* 標準規定在組織背景內建立、實施、運作、維持及持續改進 ISMS 的要求。
* 本標準也包含了適合於組織需求的資訊安全風險評鑑與處理之要求。
* 本標準敘述之要求為一般性的，且適用所有組織，與其型式、規模大小或性質無關。在組織宣稱符合本標準時，排除本標準第 4 章至第 10 章所規定之任何要求，均不被接受。
#### The intended outcomes of an ISMS include:
> ISMS的預期結果包括：
1. Enhancement of information security performance;
> 1.增強資訊的安全性；
2. Fulfillment of legal compliance obligations;
> 2.履行法律合規義務；
3. Achievement of ISMS objectives.
> 3.實現ISMS目標。
### Clause 2 - Normative reference
> 條款2-規範性引用
"ISO/IEC 27000, Information technology - Security techniques - Information security
management systems - Overview and vocabulary". This document is normatively
referenced in ISO 27001:2013 standard.
> ISO/IEC 27000，資訊技術-安全技術-資訊安全管理系統-概述和詞彙。在ISO 27001：2013標準中引用。
#### 引用標準補充
* 下列參考文件，在整體或部分上，在本文件裡屬規範性的參考且對其應用是不可或缺的。
    * 有註記日期的引用標準，僅適用於引用的版本。
    * 未註記日期的引用標準，適用於該引用標準的最新版本 (包括任何修訂)。
* ISO/IEC 27000 資訊技術‐安全技術‐資訊安全管理系統‐概述與詞彙。
### Clause 3 - Terms & Definitions
> 條款3-術語和定義
The terms and definitions given in ISO/I EC 27000 apply ISO 2700 1:20 13 standard.
> ISO / I EC 27000中給出的術語和定義適用於ISO 2700 1:20 13標準。
#### 用語釋義
* 為本文件之目的，適用 ISO/IEC 27000 所明訂的用語釋義。
## Clause 4.0 Context of the organization
> 第4.0條組織的背景
* 4.1 Understanding the organization and its context
> 4.1了解組織與其背景
* 4.2 Understanding the needs and expectations of interested parties
> 4.2了解需厲害團體的需求與期望
* 4.3 Determining the scope of the information security management system
> 4.3決定資訊安全管理系統的適用範圍
* 4.4 Information security management system.
> 4.4資訊安全管理系統

#### Clause 4.1 Understanding the organization and its context
> 第4.1節了解組織及其背景

This clause requires organization to:
* Determine external issues;
* Determine internal issues;
* All issues should be relevant to organization's purpose;
* Consider issues that affect organization's ability to achieve the intended outcome of ISMS.
> 考慮影響組織實現ISMS的預期結果的能力問題。
##### 4.1 補充
* 總而言之就是組織應決定與其目的相關，且會影響其ISMS 預期結果的達成能力之外部與內部問題。
* 這些問題的決定，請參考 ISO 31000：2009 的條款 5.3 中建立組織外部與內部環境的考量

#### Clause 4.2 Understanding the needs and expectations of interested parties
> 第4.2條了解利害相關團體的需求與期望

This clause requires the organization to determine:
> 本條款要求組織確定：
1. Interested parties that are relevant to the ISMS;
> 1.與ISMS有關的利害相關團體；
2. Requirements of these interested parties relevant to information security. These requirements include:
> 2.與資訊安全有關的這些利害相關團體之要求。要求包括：
* Legal requirements;
> 法律要求
* Regulatory requirements;
> 法規要求
* Contractual obligations; and Other requirements identified by organization.
> 除了契約義務;必須和組織確定是否有其他要求。

### Clause 4.3 Determining the scope of the ISMS
This clause requires the organization to Determine the boundaries and applicability of the ISMS to establish its scope.For determining the scope consider:
> 本條要求組織應決定 ISMS 的界線與適用性，以建立其適用範圍。當決定適用範圍時，組織應考量以下幾點：
1. the external and internal issues referred to in 4.1
> 1. 4.1中提到的外部與內部問題
2. the requirements referred to in 4.
> 2. 4.2中提到的要求
3. interfaces and dependencies between activities performed
> 3. 在組織與其他組織執行的活動之間的接合與互賴關係。

This clause also requires that the scope must be available as documented information.
> 此適用範圍應予以文件化資訊並易於取得。

The documented information related to scope of ISMS is kept in ISMS manual or as a separate scope document.
> 與ISMS範圍有關的文檔資訊保存在ISMS手冊中或作為單獨的範圍文檔。

### Clause 4.4 Information security management system (ISMS)
This clause requires the organization to:
1. Establish ISMS,
2. Implement ISMS,
3. Maintain ISMS, and
4. Continually improve ISMS, in accordance with the requirements of this ISO 27001:2013 standard.
> 組織應依據本標準的要求，以建立、實施、維持和持續改進ISMS。
### Approach of Clauses 4.1 to 4.3

![](https://i.imgur.com/6hbKtuj.png)
* 4.1了解組織及其背景並識別外部和內部問題，以及當前狀態
* 4.2了解有關方面的需求和期望
    * 確定利益相關方
    * 確定利益相關方的需求和期望
* 4.3確定ISMS的範圍
    * 考慮ISAM範圍並將上述步驟文件化並輸出成文檔保存

## Clause 5.0 Leadership
* 5.1 Leadership and commitment
* 5.2 ISMS Policy
* 5.3 Organizational roles, responsibilities and authorities

### Clause 5.1 Leadership and commitment
This clause requires the Top Management to demonstrate leadership and commitment with respect to ISMS by:
> 本條款要求最高管理者通過以下方式表現出對ISMS的領導和承諾：
1. Ensuring the information security policy and objectives are established; Policy and objectives should be compatible with the strategy of the organization;
> 1.確保資訊安全政策與目標已建立，並且和組織的策略方向是相容的;
2. Ensuring the integration of the ISMS requirements into the organization's processes;
> 2.確保 ISMS 的要求已融入組織過程中；
3. Ensuring that the resources needed for ISMS are available;
> 3.確保 ISMS 所需的資源可取得；
4. Communicating the importance of effective ISMS and of conforming to ISMS requirements;
> 4.傳達有效資訊安全管理的重要性，並且遵守 ISMS 的要求
5. Ensuring that the ISMS achieves its intended outcomes;
> 5.確保ISMS達成其預期成果；
6. Directing and supporting persons to contribute to the effectiveness of the ISMS;
> 6.指導和支援人員，使其為ISMS的有效性做出貢獻；
7. Promoting continual improvement;
> 7.促進持續改進；
8. Supporting other relevant management roles to demonstrate their leadership.
> 8.支援其他的相關管理角色，讓其展現出在職責運用上之領導力。
### Clause 5.2 ISMS Policy

Establish an information security policy that:
> 高階管理者應建立一個資訊安全政策應該符合以下幾點：
* is appropriate to the purpose of the organization;
> 符合組織目的；
* includes information security objectives or  provides the framework for setting such objectives;
> 包含資訊安全目標 (見6.2)，或提供訂立資訊安全目標的框架；
* includes a commitment to satisfy applicable requirements;
> 包含對滿足有關資訊安全之適用要求的承諾；以及
* includes a commitment to continual improvement of the ISMS.
> 包括對ISMS持續改進的承諾。
* This policy must be available as documented information.
> 資訊安全政策應：為文件化資訊並可取得；
* Communicate this policy within the organization.
> 在組織內流通。
* Provide to interested parties, as appropriate.
> 適當時，利害相關團體可取得。

The information security policy is documented and kept in ISMS manual.
> 資訊安全策略已記錄並保存在ISMS手冊中。

### Sample Information Security Policy
![](https://i.imgur.com/K9zHANE.png)

### Clause 5.3 Organizational roles, responsibilities and authorities
Ensure responsibilities and authorities for roles relevant to information security are assigned and communicated.
> 高階管理者應確保有關資訊安全的角色之責任與職權已分配和傳達。

The responsibility and authority must be assigned by the top management for:
> 高階管理者應分配責任與職權：
1. Ensuring that the ISMS conforms to ISO 2700 1:20 13 requirements.
> 1.確保 ISMS 遵守本標準的要求；以及
2. Reporting on the performance of the information security management system to top management and within the organization.
> 2.報告 ISMS 的績效給高階管理者。(高階管理者也可分配責任與職權，
在組織內可報告 ISMS 之績效。)

## Clause 6.0 Planning
* 6.1 Actions to address risks and opportunities
> 6.1風險與機會的應對措施
* 6.2 Information security objectives and planning to achieve them
> 6.2資訊安全目標與實現的計畫

### Clause 6.1 Actions to address risks and opportunities


Clause 6.1.1 General
ㆍConsider the internal and external issues as well as requirements regarding needs and expectations of interested parties to determine the risks and opportunities that need to be addressed to:
>當計劃 ISMS 時，組織應考量 4.1 所提到的問題與4.2 所提到的要求，並且決定需要應對的風險與機會，用以確保ISMS可以達成其預期結果並
* prevent, or reduce, undesired effects;
> 預防或減輕不良影響
* achieve continual improvement.
> 達成持續改進
#### 組織因應計畫
* Plan actions to address risks and opportunities.
> 因應這些風險與機會的措施，以及
* Plan how to integrate and implement the actions into ISMS processes.
>如何在其ISMS過程中融入並實施這些措施，以及
* Plan how to evaluate the effectiveness of these actions.
>如何評估這些措施的有效性

### Clause 6.1.2 Information security risk assessment
Define and apply an information security risk assessment process that:
> 組織應明訂一個資訊安全風險評鑑的過程
1. Establishes and maintains information security risk criteria, including:
> 建立與維持資訊安全風險的標準，其中包含了
* the risk acceptance criteria;
>可接受的風險標準
* criteria for performing information security risk assessments;
>執行資訊安全風險評鑑的標準
2. Ensures that repeated information security risk assessments produce consistent, valid and comparable results;
> 確保重複的資訊安全風險評鑑能產出一致的、有效的和可比較的結果；
3. Identifies infor mation security risks:
>識別資訊安全風險
* apply risk assessment process to identify risk associated with CIA for information with in scope of ISMS;
>適用的資訊安全評鑑過程，以識別與ISMS 範圍內之資訊機密性、完整性與可用性損害有關之風險；
* identify the risk owners;
> 識別風險負責人。
4. Analyses the information security risks by assessing potential consequences and likelihood of occurrence and determining the level of risk;
> 分析資訊安全風險
    1.評鑑會產生的潛在後果，如果在6.1.2 c) 1)識別的風險發生時；
    2.評鑑在6.1.2 c) 1)識別的風險，其實際發生的可能性；
    3.決定風險程度。
5. Evaluates the information security risks:
> 評估資訊安全風險
* compare the results of risk analysis with the risk criteria;
> 比較被分析的風險與在6.1.2 a)建立的風險標準
* prioritize the analyzed risks for risk treatment.
> 把被分析的風險區分出風險處理的優先順序。
6. Retain documented information about the information security risk assessment process.
> 組織應保存有關資訊安全風險評鑑過程的文件化資訊。
7. ldentify and evaluate options for the treatment of risks, and prepare a Statement of Applicability.
> 確定和評估風險處理方案，並編寫適用性聲明。

### Clause 6.1.3 Information security risk treatment
This sub clause requires the organization to define and apply an information security risk treatment process to:
> 組織應明訂與適用一個資訊安全處理過程，用以：

1. select appropriate information security risk treatment options, taking account of the risk assessment results;
> 選擇適當的資訊安全風險處理之選項，將風險評鑑結果列入考量；
2. determine all controls that are necessary to implement the information security risk treatment option(s) chosen;
> 決定在實施選用的資訊安全處理選項時，必需的所有管制項；(組織可依據需要設計管制，或從任何來源識別它們。)
3. compare the controls determined vs. controls already given in Annex-A of the standard ;don't omit necessary controls; Annex A of ISO 27001:2013 standard contains a comprehensive list of control objectives and controls. This list is not exhaustive, therefore,you may need additional control objectives and controls.
> 比較在上述6.1.3 b)決定的管制與附錄A 的，且確認沒有忽略到必要的管制；
4. produce a Statement of Applicability that contains applicability of controls and justification for inclusions, or exclusions of controls from Annex-A;
> 創作一個適用性的聲明，要包含必需的管制(見6.1.3 b) 與 c)，以及無論是否進行實施，包含之的正當理由，還有附錄A的管制排除之正當理由；
5. formulate an information security risk treatment plan; and
> 制定一個資訊安全風險處理計畫；
6. obtain risk owners' approval of the information security risk treatment plan and acceptance of the residual information security risks 
> 獲得風險負責人對資訊安全風險處理計畫的核准，以及接受殘留的資訊安全風險。

Retain documented information about the information security risk treatment process.
> 組織應保存資訊安全風險處理過程的文件化資訊。

#### Steps for establishing risk assessment
1. Define a systematic approach to risk assessment;
2. Identify the risks;
3. Assess the risks;
4. Identify and evaluate options for the treatment of risks;
5. Select control objectives and controls for the treatment of risks;
6. Obtain management approval of the proposed residual risks and operate ISMS.
![](https://i.imgur.com/evKdU2o.png)

### Clause 6.2 Requires that organization must establish information security objectives at relevant functions and levels.
> 組織應在相關的職能與層級上，建立資訊安全目標。

This clause also requires that the information security objectives must:
> 資訊安全目標應：
* be consistent with the information security policy;
> 與資訊安全政策一致；
* be measurable;
> 可測量(如果可行時)；
* consider applicable IS requirements, and results from risk assessment and risk treatment;
> 考量適用的資訊安全要求，以及風險評鑑與處理結果；
* be communicated;
> 經過溝通，且
* be updated periodically (preferably once in a year).
> 適當時作更新。
> 
The documented information on Information security objectives must be retained.
> 組織應保存資訊安全目標的文件化資訊。
> 
For planning how to achieve ISMS objectives, determine:
> 當計劃如何達成其資訊安全目標時，組織應決定：
* what will be done;
> 要做什麼；
* what resources will be required;
> 需要什麼資源；
* who will be responsible;
> 誰要負責；
* when it will be completed; and
> 何時完成；且
* how the results will be evaluated;
> 如何評估結果。

## Clause 7.0 Support
7.1 Resources
7.2 Competence
7:3 Awareness
7.4 Communication
7.5 Documented information
![](https://i.imgur.com/jyoRUMJ.png)
### Clause 7.1 Resources
This clause requires that organization must determine and provide the
resources needed for:
> 組織應決定與提供用來建立、實施、維持和持續改進 ISMS 所需的資源
1. Establishment of ISMS
2. Implementation of ISMS
3. Maintenance of ISMS, and
4. Continual improvement of the ISMS.

Organization should Provide resources to:
1. Establish, operate and maintain ISMS;
2. Support procedures as per business requirements;
3. Address legal, regulatory and contractual obligations;
4. Maintain security by application of controls;
5. Carry out reviews and act on findings;
6. Improve the effectiveness of ISMS.

### Clause 7.2 Competence
>條款 7.2 人員能力

As per this clause, organization must
1. Determine the necessary competence of person doing work that affects information security performance of the organization;
>  決定會影響資訊安全績效，受其管制的工作人員所必需的能力；
2. Ensure persons are competent on the basis of: a. Education b. Training c. Experience;
> 確保這些人員能勝任，以適當的教育、訓練或經驗為根據；
3. Where applicable, take actions to acquire the necessary competence, and evaluate the effectiveness of the actions taken; Action may include providing training, mentoring, re-assignment of current employees, recruiting competent persons, etc. Evaluate the effectiveness of the training provided and other actions taken;
> 適用時，採取措施以取得必需的能力，且評估採取的措施之有效性；以及
4. Retain appropriate documented information as evidence of competence. Retain the records of educational qualifications, training, skills, experience of the employees.
> 保存適當的文件化資訊當作能力的證據。(適用的措施可能包含，舉例來說，對目前員工提供訓練、監督或調動；或是僱用有能力的人員或與其締約。)

### Clause 7.3 Awareness
This clause requires that the persons in the organization
must be aware of:
>受組織管制的工作人員應認知到：
1. The information security policy;
> 資訊安全政策
2. Their contribution to the effectiveness of ISMS and the benefits of improved information security performance; and
> 對 ISMS 有效性之貢獻，包含了改進資訊安全績效之好處；以及
3. The implications of not conforming to the ISMS requirements.
> 不符合ISMS 要求的含義。

### Clause 7.4 Communication
This clause requires the organization to determine the need for internal and external communications relevant to the ISMS, including:
> 組織應決定與 ISMS 有關的內部與外部溝通之需求，包含了：
1. What to communicate?
> 要溝通什麼?
2. When to communicate?
> 何時溝通?
3. Whom to communicate?
> 和誰溝通?
4. Who shall communicate?
> 應由誰溝通?
5. The processes by which communication will be effected.
> 應實現哪種溝通過程?

## Clause 7.5 Documented Information
* Clause 7.5.1 General
* Clause 7.5.2 Creating and Updating
* Clause 7.5.3 Control of documented information
>條款 7.5.3 文件化資訊的管制

### Clause 7.5.1 General
The organization's ISMS must include documented information:
> 組織的 ISMS 應包含：
1. Required by ISO 27001:2013;
> 本標準必需的文件化資訊；以及
2. Determined by the organization as being necessary for the effectiveness of the ISMS.
> 由組織決定，ISMS 的有效性所必需的文件化資訊。

The extent of ISMS documentation can differ from one organization to another, depending on:
> 一個 ISMS 的文件化資訊之廣度會在不同組織間有所差異，因為：
1. The size of organization and its type of activities, processes, products and services;
> 組織的規模，以及其活動、過程、產品與服務的類型；
2. The complexity of processes and their interactions;
> 過程的複雜性與相互作用；以及
3. The competence of persons.
> 人員的能力。
### Clause 7.5.2 Creating and Updating
Organization should create and update documented information as per requirements of ISO 27001:2013 Information Security Management System. This sub-clause requires that When creating and updating documented information the organization must ensure:
> 當創造與更新文件化資訊時，組織應確保適當的：
1. Proper identification and description (e.g. a title, date, author, or reference number)
> 識別與描述 (例如一個標題、日期、作者、或參考編號)；
2. Proper format (e.g. language, software version, graphics) and media(e.g. paper, electronic)
> 格式 (例如語言、軟體版本、圖表) 與媒介(例如紙本、電子)；以及
3. Review and update and re-approval for suitability and adequacy.Prior to issue, documented information should be approved by IS Head or authorized person for adequacy and suitability.
> 適用性與充足性的審查和核准。發布之前，應由IS負責人或授權人員批准文件化信息以確保其適當性和適當性。

### Sample list of documented information
Sample list of documented information required for ISMS is given below, however this is not an exhaustive list
> 以下列出了ISMS所需的書面信息的示例列表，但這並不是詳盡的列表
1. Documented statements of the security policy and ISMS objectives;
> 有關安全政策和ISMS目標的書面聲明；
2. The scope of the ISMS and procedures and controls supporting the ISMS;
> ISMS的範圍以及支持ISMS的程序和控制
3. Risk assessment report;
> 風險評估報告
4. Risk treatment plan;
> 風險處理計劃
5. Documented procedures for effective planning, operation and control of information security processes;
> 有效計劃，操作和控制信息安全流程的書面程序；
6. Records for compliance with ISO 27001:2013 requirements;
> 符合ISO 27001：2013要求的記錄；
7. Statement of Applicability;
> 適用性聲明；
8. Policies and procedures to establish controls on information security as per established ISMS.
> 按照既定的ISMS建立信息安全控制措施的政策和程序。

### Clause 7.5.3 Control of documented information
Documented information must be controlled to ensure its:
> ISMS 與本標準必需的文件化資訊應受管制以確保：
* Availability and suitability for use;
> 在需要的地點與時間，可取得且適當使用；
* Adequate protection from loss of confidentiality, improper use, or loss of integrity, etc.
> 受到充分的維護 (例如避免機密性的損害、使用不當、或完整性的損害)；

For the control of documented information, address the following activities:
> 對於文件化資訊的管制，適用時，組織應應對下列的活動：
* Distribution, access, retrieval and use of documented information;
> 分配、存取、修復、使用；
* Storage and preservation (including the preservation of legibility);
> 貯藏與保存，包含保存易讀性；
* Control of changes and current revision status;
> 變更管制 (例如版本的變更)；以及
* Retention and disposition.
> 保留與廢除。

Ensure information of external origin, as identified by IS Head, are subjected to same level of controls.
>確保由IS Head識別的外部來源資訊受到相同級別的控制。

Ensure the recent version of documented information is available at the points of use.
> 確保在使用時可獲得最新版本的文檔資訊。

Ensure distribution of information is controlled. Prevent unintended use of obsolete information.
> 確保資訊分配受到控制。防止意外使用過時的資訊。

Apply suitable identification; and ensure access to documented information for review or change.
> 申請適當的身份證明；並確保可以訪問文檔資訊以進行查看或更改。

Record control (Retain documented information: main points)
> 記錄控制（保留記錄的信息：要點）
* Established and maintained
* Evidence
* Controlled
* Legal requirements
* Legible, identifiable and retrievable.
>建立和維護、證據、可受控、符合法律要求、清晰，可識別和可檢索。

Maintain Documents (Document controls for:
> 維護文檔（用於以下方面的文檔控件：
* Identification,
* Storage,
* Protection,
* Retrieval,
* Retention time, and
* Disposition of documented information.
> 識別、儲存、保護、恢復、保留時間、以及處理文件化信息。

#### The procedure for control of documented information
should include following key points:
1. Information approval;
2. Review and update of information;
3. Identification of revision and changes;
4. Most recent version available at point of use;
5. Legible and identifiable;
6. External information control;
7. Controlled distribution;
8. Obsolete information - prevention of use;
9. Access to information for view and changes.
>
    * 資訊批准
    * 審查和更新資訊
    * 識別修訂和變更
    * 使用時可獲得最新版本
    * 清晰可辨
    * 外部資訊, 控制
    * 控制分配
    * 過時的資訊需要禁止使用
    * 資訊存取以進行查看和更改
## Clause 8.0 Operation
* 8.1 Operational planning and control
* 8.2 Information security risk assessment
* 8.3 Information security risk treatment.

### 8.1 Operational planning and control

This clause requires the organization to:
> 8.1 運作的計畫與管制
1. Plan, implement and control the processes;
> 計劃、實施和控制過程;
2. Implement the actions to address risks and opportunities; as described in clause 6.1;
> 實施這些行動以解決風險和機會; 如第6.1條所述;
3. Implement the risk treatment plan and controls to achieve the IS objectives; as described in clause 6.2;
> 執行風險處理計劃及控制措施,以達致國際信息系統目標;
4. Maintain documented information to establish confidence that the processes are carried out as planned;
> 通過採取控制措施維持安全；
5. Control planned changes and review the consequences of unintended changes, taking action to mitigate any adverse effects, as necessary;
> 進行審查並根據發現採取行動；
6. Ensure that outsourced processes are determined and controlled.
> 提高ISMS的有效性。

The organization should implement procedures and other controls as applicable for its ISMS based on ISO 27001:2013 standard.
>組織應根據ISO 27001：2013標準實施適用於其ISMS的程序和其他控制措施。

#### 總結
* 組織應計畫、實施與管制可符合資訊安全要求，及實施在 6.1 決定的措施時所需要的過程。組織也應實施計畫，以達成在 6.2 決定的資訊安全目標。
* 組織應依照計畫實現過程所必需的信心程度，保存文件化資訊。
* 組織應管制計畫的變更，並審查無預期的變更會帶來的後果，在必要時，採取措施以減輕任何不良影響。
* 組織應確保外包過程是確定的並受管制。

### 8.2 Information security risk assessment
* Perform information security risk assessments at planned intervals or when significant changes are proposed or occur, taking account of the criteria established. Criteria includes the risk acceptance criteria, and criteria for performing information security risk assessments.
> 組織應在計劃之期間內，或是當重大的變更被提出或發生時，執行資訊安全風險評鑑，並考量在 6.1.2 a) 建立的標準。
* Retain documented information of the results of risk assessments.
> 組織應保存資訊安全風險評鑑結果的文件化資訊。

### Clause 8.3: Information security risk treatment
This clause requires that the organization must;
* Implement the information security risk treatment plan.
> 組織應實施資訊安全風險處理的計畫。
* Retain documented information of the results of the information security risk treatment.
> 組織應保存資訊安全風險處理結果的文件化資訊。

## Clause 9.0 Performance Evaluation
* 9.1 Monitoring, measurement, analysis and evaluation
* 9.2 Internal audit
* 9.3 Management review

### Clause 9.1 Monitoring, measurement, analysis and evaluation
> 9.1 監督、量測、分析與評估
Evaluate the information security performance and the effectiveness of the ISMS.
> 組織應評估資訊安全的績效與 ISMS 的有效性。
Determine:
1. What needs to be monitored and measured, including IS processes and controls?;
2. The methods for monitoring, measurement, analysis and evaluation;
3. When the monitoring and measuring will be performed?
4. Who will monitor and measure?
5. When the results from monitoring and measurement will be analyzed and evaluated ?; and
6. Who will analyze and evaluate these results?
Retain documented information as evidence of the monitoring and measurement results.
> 組織應保存適當的文件化資訊，作為監督與量測結果的證據。

The methods for monitoring, measurement, analysis and evaluation should produce comparable and reproducible results to ensure valid results.
> 監視，測量，分析和評估的方法應產生可比較且可重複的結果，以確保有效的結果。

### 9.2 Internal audit

Conduct ISMS internal audits at planned intervals to determine whether the ISMS meets organization's own requirements and ISO 27001:20 13 requirements. Also ensure that the ISMS is effectively implemented and maintained.
> 按計劃的時間間隔進行ISMS內部審核，以確定ISMS是否滿足組織自身的要求和ISO 27001：20 13的要求。還應確保ISMS得到有效實施和維護。
1. Plan, establish, implement and maintain an audit program as per documented procedure.Procedure includes the audit frequency, methods, responsibilities, planning requirements and reporting.
> 按照書面程序計劃，建立，實施和維護審核計劃，程序包括審核頻率，方法，職責，計劃要求和報告。
2. When making the audit program, consider the importance of the processes concerned and the results of previous audits.
> 在製定審核計劃時，請考慮相關流程的重要性以及之前審核的結果。
3. Define the audit criteria and scope for each audit.
> 定義每次審核的審核標準和範圍。
4. Select independent auditors and conduct audits that ensure objectivity and the impartiality of the audit process.
> 選擇獨立的審核員並進行審核，以確保審核過程的客觀性和公正性。
5. Ensure that the results of the audits are reported to the management.
> 確保將審核結果報告給管理層
6. Retain documented information as evidence of the audit program and the audit results.
> 保留記錄的信息，作為審核計劃和審核結果的證據。

Internal audit should include verification of the actions taken and the reporting of verification results. Verify whether actions as well as improvement activities are taken
without undue delay.
>內部審核應包括對所採取措施的驗證以及驗證結果的報告。驗證是否採取了行動以及改進活動毫不遲延地。

#### 補充
1. 組織應在計劃之期間內執行內部稽核，以提供資訊，指出ISMS 是否符合
    * 組織本身有關 ISMS 的要求；以及本標準的要求；
    * 有效地實施與維護。
2. 組織應： 計畫、建立、實施與維護一個稽核流程，包含了頻率、方法、責任、計畫中的要求與報告。稽核流程應考量相關過程的重要性，以及先前稽核的結果；
    * 為每一場稽核明訂稽核標準與適用範圍；
    * 選擇稽核員並執行稽核，以確保稽核過程的客觀與公正；
    * 確保稽核結果已向相關管理者報告；以及
    * 保存文件化資訊，作為稽核流程與稽核結果的證據。
### 9.3 Management review
Top Management must review the organization's ISMS at planned intervals to ensure its continuing suitability, adequacy and effectiveness.
>最高管理者必須按計劃的時間間隔檢查組織的ISMS，以確保其持續的適用性，充分性和有效性。
The inputs to the management review must include:
1. The status of actions from previous management reviews;
> 先前管理審查的措施之狀態
2. Changes in external and internal issues that are relevant to the ISMS;
> 有關 ISMS 的外部與內部問題之變更；
3. Feedback on the information security performance, including trends in:(管理審查應包含的考量事項：)
    * nonconformities and corrective actions;
    >不符合事項與矯正措施；
    * monitoring and measurement results;
    >監督與量測結果；
    * results of ISMS audits and reviews; and
    >稽核結果；以及
    * fulfillment of information security objectives;；
    >資訊安全目標的實現；
4. Feedback from interested parties;
> 利害相關團體的回饋；
5. Results of risk assessment and status of risk treatment plan, including vulnerabilities or threats not adequately addressed in the previous risk assessment; and
> 風險評鑑的結果與風險處理計畫的狀態；以及
6. Opportunities for continual improvement.
> 持續改進的機會；
The management review should also consider the techniques, products or procedures to improve the ISMS performance and effectiveness, as well as any changes that could affect
the ISMS.
> 管理評審還應考慮改善ISMS績效和有效性的技術，產品或程序，以及可能影響其安全性的任何變更。
#### Management Review Output
The outputs of review must include:
* Decisions related to continual improvement opportunities for effectiveness of system;
> 與持續改進機會有關的決策，以提高系統的有效性；
* Any needs for changes to the ISMS.
> 更改ISMS的任何需求。
* The review output should also include any need for modification of procedures that effect information security, including changes to:
> 審查輸出還應包括對影響信息安全的程序的任何修改，包括對以下方面的更改：
    * Business requirements(業務需求)
    * Security requirements(安全要求)
    * Business processes(業務流程)
    * Regulatory or legal environment(法規或法律環境)
    * Levels of risk and/or levels of risk acceptance(風險水平和/或風險接受水平)
7. Retain documented information as an evidence of the results of management reviews.(For example: minutes of meeting).
> 保留文件化信息，作為管理評審結果的證據（例如：會議記錄）。

## Clause 10.0 Improvement
10.1 Nonconformity and corrective action
10.2 Continual improvement

### 10.1 Nonconformity and corrective action
> 10.1 不符合事項與矯正措施
When a nonconformity occurs, the organization must:
> 當出現不符合規定的情況時,組織必須:
1. React to the nonconformity and take action to control and correct it, and deal with the consequences;
> 適用時，對不符合事項作出回應：採取措施管制與矯正之；以及處理後果；
2. Evaluate the need for action to eliminate the causes of nonconformity by:
> 估消除不符合事項的原因之措施需求，為了使其不再發生或是在別處發生，經由：
    * reviewing the nonconformity;
    > 審查不符合事項
    * determining the causes of the nonconformity; and
    > 決定不符合事項的原因；以及
    * determining if similar nonconformities exist, or could potentially occur;
    > 決定是否有相似的不符合事項存在，或有發生的潛在性；
3. Implement the action needed;
> 實施任何需要的措施；
4. Review the effectiveness of corrective action taken; 
> 審查任何採取的矯正措施之有效性；以及
5. Make changes to the information security management system, if necessary.
> 必要時，對 ISMS 作變更；

Retain documented information as evidence of:
> 保留有文件記錄的資料,以證明:
* the nature of the nonconformities and any subsequent actions taken; and
> 不符合事項的本質與任何採取的後續措施；以及
* the results of corrective action.
> 任何矯正措施的結果。
Corrective action is taken to eliminate the causes of nonconformity, so that it does not recur or occur elsewhere. Corrective actions must be appropriate to the effects of the
nonconformities .
> 採取糾正措施來消除不合格的原因，使其不再發生或不再發生在別處。 糾正措施必須適合於不合格的影響。

### 10.2 Continual improvement
This last but most important clause of ISO 27001:2013 requires the organization to Continually improve the suitability, adequacy and effectiveness of the information
security management system.
> 組織應持續改進 ISMS 的適切性、充份性與有效性。
Continual improvement can be achieved through following means:
> 可透過以下途徑持續改善:
1. Information security policy;
2. Information security objectives;
3. Audit results;
4. Analysis of monitored events;
> 對被監測事件的分析
5. Corrective and preventive actions; and
> 糾正預防措施;
6. Management review.

